com.viaoa.hub
Class HubData

java.lang.Object
  com.viaoa.hub.HubData
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class HubData
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Internally used by Hub to store objects. Shared Hubs will use this same object.
A Vector and Hashtable are used to store the objects.

vector

changeCount

protected transient int changeCount
Counter that is incremented on: add(), insert(), remove(), setting shared hub, remove(), move(), sort(), select(). This can be used to know if a hub has been changed without requiring the set up of a HubListener.

This is used by OA.JSP components to know if a frame should be updated. See com.viaoa.html.OATable.

newListCount

protected transient int newListCount
Counter that is incremented when a new list of objects is loaded. Incremented by select, setSharedHub, and when detail hubs list is changed to match the master hub's activeObject.
This can be used to know if a hub has been changed without requiring the set up of a HubListener.

This is used by JSP components to know if a frame should be updated.
See com.viaoa.html.OATable and com.viaoa.html.OANav
